# Workflow and PR

## GitHub links
- **Never** give the user a link to GitHub (compare URLs, repo URLs, PR links, etc.).
- If a PR or comparison would normally be shared via link, do not include it.

## Pull requests
- When you finish a change, let the user now. He will prompt you to make a commit + push.
   - Commit + Push to the DEV branch, not a new branch.
- Create the PR in the dev branch, this will be merged to prod. ALWAYS CREATE IN DEV BRANCH
- Use `gh pr create` (or the project’s normal PR flow) to open the PR.
- Name the pull request using the following format: HHMM(A/P)MMDDYY, where A or P is AM/PM.
   - An example is 0610P031226, which represents 6:10 PM on 3/12/26
- Do not suggest the user “open a link” to create the PR; create it yourself when possible.
